{"updated_at": "2012-03-11T22:10:15Z", "repo": "rails", "created_at": "2012-03-11T22:10:15Z", "owner": "rails", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4442750", "id": 4442750, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5345", "issue_id": 5345, "user": {"repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/repos", "type": "User", "html_url": "https://github.com/jeremy", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/subscriptions", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/following{/other_user}", "gravatar_id": "24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/gists{/gist_id}", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/24d2f8804e6bb4b7ea6bd11e0a586470?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F84d9ee44e457ddef7f2c4f25dc8fa865.png", "id": 199, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/events{/privacy}", "login": "jeremy", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/received_events", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jeremy/followers"}, "body": "I understand the gut feeling about data-structureness -- that \"slice\" means taking apart a concrete thing and returning a sub-part. Slicing an object, literally speaking, could mean returning a proxy object that only responds to the sliced messages, for example.\r\n\r\nI think `#attrs` would be a good alternative, echoing `attr_reader` and `attr_accessor`.\r\n\r\n\"Send these method names to the object and map them to their return values.\"", "_id": {"$oid": "5238198abd3543c15100e1a7"}, "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5345#issuecomment-4442750"}
